==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Ravine
<hw>Ra*vine"</hw> <pr>(r⟦adot⟧*v⟦emac⟧n")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.,
a place excavated by a torrent, a ravine, fr. <ets>ravir</ets> to snatch
or tear away, L. <ets>rapere</ets>; cf. L. <ets>rapina</ets> rapine. See
<er>Ravish</er>, and cf. <er>Rapine</er>, <er>Raven</er> prey.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A torrent of water.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cotgrave.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A deep and narrow hollow, usually worn by a stream
or torrent of water; a gorge; a mountain cleft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

